00:04:10.950 --> 00:04:16.880
, Twitter, and now the AI social media community.

00:04:17.050 --> 00:04:19.810
And so, thinking about how that community has migrated or not

00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:20.880
migrated...

00:04:20.880 --> 00:04:24.880
That community has not migrated very well.

00:04:25.010 --> 00:04:26.500
And I think there are a few reasons...

00:04:26.500 --> 00:04:27.860
There's a lot of reasons for that.

00:04:27.890 --> 00:04:28.880
And there's also a lot of mystery.

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:31.620
Like, if I knew all the answers, then I would

00:04:31.620 --> 00:04:33.880
already have them all in blue sky.

00:04:34.090 --> 00:04:37.180
But so, one of the things is the industry connections in

00:04:37.180 --> 00:04:38.880
our research community.

00:04:38.880 --> 00:04:42.380
So, of course, a lot of what is happening in

00:04:42.380 --> 00:04:45.880
AI is to do with what is happening in industry.

00:04:46.070 --> 00:04:49.250
And that what is happening in research is also connected to what

00:04:49.250 --> 00:04:50.880
is happening in industry.

00:04:50.880 --> 00:04:53.270
And so, I think there's a general sense that,

00:04:53.270 --> 00:04:54.600
you know, if you want to be in the know,

00:04:54.600 --> 00:04:55.930
if you want to know what's happening in industry, if

00:04:56.010 --> 00:04:57.040
you want to know what's happening in industry, if you

00:04:57.090 --> 00:04:59.250
want those kind of connections, if you're one of these

00:04:59.250 --> 00:05:02.850
, like, sorry, but like, grifters and

00:05:02.850 --> 00:05:05.880
